27/07/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Defence Minister Teodor Atanasiu was quoted on Tuesday (26 July) as saying that Romania and the United States are close to an agreement on the deployment of US bases in the country. UPI, citing the US military publication Stars and Stripes, said talks could be completed by September. Romania is offering the Pentagon five facilities. Atanasiu said there is a consensus among the public, political parties, the government and parliament about welcoming US troops to Romanian territory. (UPI - 26/07/05)
